main event: A control tower operator on Wake Island reported observing two bluish-white vapor trails with a buzzing sound on 13 June 1957.
interesting points: The trails were observed forming at about 600 feet and rapidly dissipated after several seconds.,The operator described the sound as similar to a twinjet, but not as loud or high-pitched.,Each vapor trail was about 225 feet long with a break of 25 feet between them.,The trails had an estimated speed of about 500 mph.,The observation lasted for 255 degrees.
witness description: A control tower operator with 11-1/2 years of experience.
